<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 02 at 5:39PM CDT until July 02 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 615 PM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN OLDHAM...SOUTHWESTERN SHERMAN...SOUTHERN DALLAM...
NORTHWESTERN MOORE AND HARTLEY COUNTIES...
At 538 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 5 miles south of Conlen to 5 miles south of Dalhart to
8 miles southeast of Amistad, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Dalhart, Hartley, Romero and Conlen.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
